data.name: lblQuality.Text
data.value:
Quality is from 0-100, where 100 is highest quality. These quality settings will set the standard of encoding. The default quality setting is set to 80, 52 when a custom quantification table is selected, marked by "(CQC)".
This setting cannot be used when the LSB method is selected.

data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
There are two methods of steganography in this programme.
These two options are described here:
Least Significant Bit (LSB) - this method of steganography places the information in the least two signifcant bits of the pixels.
Graph Theory Method (GT) - this method of steganography is more advanced than LSB and is more discrete in terms of encoding than LSB.

data.name: General.Text
data.value:
This programme uses two methods of steganography.
When wanting to conceal information, this programme gives you two methods of doing this: a least significant bit method and a graph theoretic approach.
When proceeding with encoding or decoding you will be asked where you want to save your image to.

data.name: lblHuffman.Text
data.value:
Type in your codes, as necessary if using a custom huffman code. Otherwise the Huffman tables can be left alone and a default will be used.
There are four radio buttons to switch between the four different channels and if more rows are needed, these can be added.
However, if you save something incorrectly in this setting, you will have to start over.

data.name: Quantization.Text
data.value:
To use a custom quantization table, just type in the corresponding box. If not using a custom quantization table, the default tables will be used.
The size of each quantization table is always 64 for both the luminance and chromium channels.
However, if you save something incorrectly in this setting, you will have to start over.
